Firefighters were deployed to an informal settlement just after midnight. CAPE TOWN - Two children have died and four shacks were razed in a firein Fisantekraal. Firefighters were deployed toan informal settlement just after midnight. Fire and Rescue Service's Theo Layne says: At about 12:30am this morning, the citys fire service responded to Goedverwacht Street in Fisantekraal where a fire broke out. Four informal structures were destroyed and approximately 15 people were displaced.